08/12/2010
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Ahead of the upcoming snap elections, European Parliament (EP) members are urging Kosovo leaders to avoid the mistakes Albania made in the aftermath of disputed June 2009 general elections. 
The two main political parties there are still wrangling over the process, which has stalled legislative activities, especially those related to crucial EU reforms. 
Doris Pack and Ulrike Lunacek, leaders of the EP delegation that will monitor Sunday's snap vote, have called for a massive voter turnout. 
(Zeri, Kosova Sot, Koha Ditore, Express - 07/12/10)
